==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grossification
<hw>Gross`i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Gross</ets> + L. <ets>ficare</ets> (in comp.) to make. See
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of making gross or thick,
or the state of becoming so.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The swelling of the ovary of
plants after fertilization. Henslow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grossly</ent>⟦br⟧
